            <abstract id="ref3" label="Abstract">Irving Weissman (1913-1998) was a labor activist and a member of the Young Communist League before he went to fight in the Spanish Civil War. In Spain he trained and fought with the MacKenzie-Papineau Battalion. Many of the images in this collection were acquired by Weissman in the course of his service with the MacKenzie-Papineau Battalion in Spain. The collection contains combat and non-combat photographs, portraits, images of Czechoslovakian volunteers interned at the Gurs Concentration Camp in France, the U.S. veterans' fiftieth anniversary trip to Spain and a veterans memorial meeting.</abstract>
            <physdesc id="ref1" label="General Physical Description note">289 black and white photographs sized from 1 ¾ x 2 ¼ inches to 8 ½ x 11 inches and 10 negatives sized from 2 ½ x 3 ¼ to 5 ½ x 4 inches.</physdesc>
